        <!-- Two-col: Wireless Network Protocols + Mobile & Wireless Expert -->
        <div class="two-col">
          <div>
            <h3>Background</h3>

            <p>Dr. Lavian holds a Ph.D. in Computer Science from UC Berkeley, specializing in network communications, and spent nearly 20 years researching, studying, and lecturing at UC Berkeley&rsquo;s College of Engineering. He served as Principal Scientist and Principal Architect at Nortel Networks (1996&ndash;2007) and as a DARPA Principal Investigator. Dr. Lavian has over 120 <a href="/patents/">patents</a>, over 25 <a href="/scientific-publications/">scientific publications</a>, and has been retained in over 70 <a href="/cases-expert-witness-testimony/">cases</a>, including 80+ depositions, before U.S. federal courts, PTAB, ITC, and international tribunals, on behalf of over 50 law firms and corporate clients. His mobile and wireless case work includes <a href="/case/55-t-mobile-v-barkan-wireless-access-technologies/">T-Mobile v. Barkan Wireless Access Technologies</a> (U.S. Patent Nos. 8,559,369 and 9,042,306, involving wireless access technologies), <a href="/case/18-ixi-mobile-v-apple-inc/">IXI Mobile v. Apple</a> (U.S. Patent Nos. 7,426,398 and 7,295,532, involving mobile device technologies), and <a href="/cases-expert-witness-testimony/">Ericsson v. Samsung (ITC)</a> (U.S. Patent Nos. 6,772,215 and 6,519,223, involving wireless communications).</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Mobile &amp; Wireless Expert</h3>

            <p>The following are Dr. Tal Lavian&rsquo;s areas of expertise in Mobile and Wireless Technologies:</p>

            <ul>
              <li><a href="https://standards.ieee.org/ieee/802.11/5536/">Wi-Fi, IEEE 802.11,</a> MAC, PHY.</li>
              <li><a href="https://www.ietf.org/documents/149/95-802-11-Tutorial.pdf">Wireless LAN (WLAN)</a>, <a href="/communications-expert-witness/messaging-and-chat-expert-witness/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">SMS, MMS</a>, Instant Messaging (IM) chat.</li>
              <li>Wireless technologies, 3G, 4G, 5G, LTE, RF, CDMA, GSM, and RAN.</li>
              <li>Handsets, mobile devices, smartphones.</li>
              <li>Bluetooth, IEEE 802.15, WPAN,cellular networks, wireless systems, architectures.</li>
              <li>Standards, systems, and backend infrastructure.</li>
            </ul>

            <p>Mobile and wireless technologies provide an ever-increasing number of opportunities for companies to innovate and grow. Wireless <a href="/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">telecommunications providers</a> are experiencing dramatic growth in mobile data transmission, driving demand for mobile devices supporting data-intensive consumer-based applications, such as location-based services and 3D gaming. Mobile and wireless technologies can be complex. Their associated infrastructure is crucial to mission-critical applications such as defense, emergency response, and business, including logistics, smart city, <a href="/communications-expert-witness/data-communications-expert/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">network infrastructure</a>, supply, and more.</p>

            <p>Mobile network infrastructure is based on a software-defined architecture that allows greater flexibility, increased adaptability to new capabilities, and automation, allowing wireless operators to compete better.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2>Mobile and Wireless in Patent Litigation</h2>

        <p>Dr. Lavian&rsquo;s mobile and wireless expertise covers Wi-Fi, Bluetooth, cellular systems (3G/4G/5G), RF engineering, spectrum management, IoT connectivity, mobile device architectures, <a href="/communications-expert-witness/network-security-expert/">wireless security</a>, and regulatory standards. He provides analysis and testimony in patent disputes involving these technologies before U.S. federal courts, PTAB, and the ITC.</p>

        <section class="faq-section" aria-label="Frequently asked questions about mobile and wireless expert witness services">
          <h2>Frequently Asked Questions: Mobile &amp; Wireless Expert Witness</h2>

          <details open>
            <summary>What wireless technologies is Dr. Lavian expert in?</summary>
            <p>Dr. Lavian is expert in Wi-Fi (802.11a/b/g/n/ac/ax), Bluetooth, wireless LAN protocols, mobile communications systems, wireless network architecture, and wireless device networking in the context of patent litigation.</p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Has Dr. Lavian testified in ITC wireless cases?</summary>
            <p>Yes. Dr. Lavian has provided expert witness services in International Trade Commission (ITC) Section 337 investigations involving wireless communications technologies, including smartphones and wireless networking equipment.</p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>What is Dr. Lavian&rsquo;s background in wireless communications?</summary>
            <p>Dr. Lavian has a Ph.D. from UC Berkeley and extensive research experience in wireless network protocols. His patent portfolio includes patents covering wireless communication technologies, and he has testified in wireless cases in federal courts, PTAB, and ITC proceedings.</p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>What types of wireless patent disputes has Dr. Lavian handled?</summary>
            <p>Dr. Lavian has handled patent disputes involving Wi-Fi implementations, wireless network access control, Bluetooth communication protocols, wireless roaming and handoff mechanisms, WLAN security, and mobile device connectivity architectures.</p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Can Dr. Lavian provide expert witness services for cellular and 5G patent cases?</summary>
            <p>Yes. Dr. Lavian&rsquo;s wireless expertise covers cellular network technologies including LTE and 5G NR architectures, carrier aggregation, MIMO antenna systems, and mobile network infrastructure. He can provide expert reports and testimony on cellular standard-essential patents (SEPs) and FRAND licensing disputes.</p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>What wireless companies has Dr. Lavian served as an expert witness for?</summary>
            <p>Dr. Lavian has been retained in wireless patent cases involving companies including Apple, Samsung, Qualcomm, Motorola, and other major wireless device manufacturers and semiconductor companies, providing analysis and testimony on Wi-Fi, Bluetooth, and cellular technologies.</p>
          </details>
        </section>

